name: Jeano Appleseed

tweet: @jmuhj1 Was there snow most of the Winter or did it get relatively warm between cold spells?

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @urbanehillbilly @VanceMc14 I have discovered in the 12 years I've been here than many succulents dislike heat and too dry though most can withstand dry for a while. If in bright sun & dry condition, they tend to go dormant dehydrate till rain or seasonal shade comes. I've lost many bc of hot sun.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @urbanehillbilly @VanceMc14 They grow quite well with a fairly broad range of temperatures, but here they seem to enjoy most seasons except Summer. Lack of water also is a problem after a little while because our soil gets so dry.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @jmuhj1 Wow. That IS very cold. I didn't realize it could get that cold there. Despite spending my youth in a frigid climate, I'm no longer used to it either, though I tolerate cold better than heat. We haven't had a real consistently cool Winter with cold nights in a long time.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @urbanehillbilly @VanceMc14 I suspect Winter in the canaries is also warmer than winter here, because of the ocean influence. Our winters here can be quite cold at night, on sunless days or when the jet stream shifts and brings cold air down along the coast. But it doesn't normally last very long.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @urbanehillbilly @VanceMc14 Here, they grow well & get huge, though they struggle a bit in Summer when it's hot and dry, but in the desert where @VanceMc14 is, it sounds more tricky. name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @brycedimsdale Explaining this to a person who hasn’t felt this to that extent is nearly impossible. A person wanting to help, first, has to trust what you’re saying as true even if it’s not their reality.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @brycedimsdale That’s been one of my biggest issues fighting lifelong chronic depression: trying to imagine that things can even be better. And if things settle, then remembering how dark a time it was & why I couldn’t see out of it.

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: When depression hits, a person may not be able to pull themselves out of it because that person may not be able to remember that there is a state outside depression and what it feels like. In that sense depression can be a bottomless abyss to a depressed person. https://t.co/sp516oxozv

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @northerngarden4 Kind of cross betw strawberry & kiwi but less sweet &  not very acidic. Tiny black seeds are crunchy, hardly noticeable. Skin gets bubblegum pink when it's ready & splits open when it's at its best though will get eaten by wildlife if not harvested quickly after it splits /2🛑

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @northerngarden4 As for taste & texture, it's similar to watermelon in texture except juices are gel-like, which is typical of cacti sap. Some people find it "slimy" and don't like it  bc of that. The fruit has no pricks and its thick (~5mm) skin peels easily. Less juicy than watermelon. /1

name: Jeano Appleseed
tweet: @northerngarden4 You never know if you grow it in a pot though I find the "non-monstrose" cereus peruvianus faster growing and fruits more easily. But I don't know how easily it would bloom & fruit w only Summers outdoors.
